d item was voluntarily disposed of. Time/temperature control for safety (TCS) food that is cooked, cooled, and reheated for hot holding must be reheated to 165 degrees Fahrenheit or above for 15 seconds. Corrective Action - Establishment is to reheat food items in microwave until they have reached a minimum internal temperature of 165 degrees F before placing them in the warmer. Corrected On-Site. New Violation. Correct By: 10/23/2023"}]}, {"date": "05-25-2023", "type": "Routine", "seats": "Food Service (Non-Profit)", "reportUrl": "https://ri.healthinspections.us/_templates/62/Restaurant/_report_full.cfm?inspID=4479581&domainID=62&userID=0&rtype=Restaurant&reportIDParent=0&SubType='&dsn=DHD_62&wguid=1367&wgunm=sysuser&wgdmn=630_2&logintime=%2200:00:00%20AM%22&public=1", "violations": [{"item": 39, "code": "3-307.11", "severity": "C", "text": "A sign was observed on the milk fridge stating that milk is good 5-10 days after expiration. Please smell/taste before serving. Corrective Action - Sign was removed and Establishment is to use dates posted by manufacturers. All Milk was in date during time of inspection. Corrected On-Site. New Violation. Correct By: 05/25/2023"}]}]